# distributed-deque — agent memory

Read `AGENTS.md` at the repo root for the full, maintained summary.

## What this is

Go library: **distributed deque** backed by **Redis**. One `Deque` interface; two engines — **ListDeque** (Lists, ephemeral, low latency) and **StreamDeque** (Streams, durable, ack-aware). See `README.md` for architecture, multi-region, and production notes.

- **Module:** `github.com/williamntlam/distributed-deque`
- **Package name:** `distributeddeque`

## Implementation status

| Area | Status |
|------|--------|
| `README.md` | Design doc (source of truth for API goals) |
| `errors.go` | Done: `ErrEmpty`, `ErrClosed`; helpers `isEmpty` / `isClosed` (package-private) |
