| Roadmap | `ErrReadOnly`, `ErrTimeout`, `context.Context` on ops, health helper |

## Error semantics

- **`ErrEmpty`** — non-blocking pop/shift when deque has no elements (client still usable).
- **`ErrClosed`** — client shut down (e.g. after `Close()`); ops rejected until a new client is created.
- Distinguish from Redis/network errors and `context` cancellation in implementations.

## Toolchain (important)

- **`go.mod` currently:** `go 1.26` (requires matching toolchain).
- User env: **Ubuntu 24.04 WSL**; may have **apt** `golang-go` → 1.22 at `/usr/bin/go` and/or **`/usr/local/go`** for newer Go.
- `go mod tidy` fails with `toolchain not available` when `go.mod` version > installed `go version` — align `go` line with `go version`, or install Go (apt: `golang-1.24-go`; official: `go*.linux-amd64.tar.gz` to `/usr/local/go`, not `.src.tar.gz`).
- Put `/usr/local/go/bin` **before** `/usr/bin/go` on `PATH` when using tarball install.
- Never commit `go*.tar.gz` in the repo root.

## Dependencies

- `github.com/redis/go-redis/v9` (in `go.mod`)

